251
0:11:55.311,000 --> 0:11:57,000
He goes, "Well Jeff Hawkins, the CEO, says,

252
0:11:57.367,000 --> 0:12:01,000
'If any task on the Palm Pilot takes more than three taps of the stylus,

253
0:12:01.6,000 --> 0:12:03,000
it's too long, and it has to be redesigned.'

254
0:12:04.622,000 --> 0:12:05,000
So I'm the tap counter."

255
0:12:06.414,000 --> 0:12:07,000
So, I'm going to show you an example

256
0:12:08.2,000 --> 0:12:1,000
of a company that does not have a tap counter.

257
0:12:10.846,000 --> 0:12:11,000
(Laughter)

258
0:12:12.133,000 --> 0:12:13,000
This is Microsoft Word.

259
0:12:13.728,000 --> 0:12:17,000
Ok, when you want to create a new blank document in Word --

260
0:12:17.886,000 --> 0:12:18,000
it could happen.

261
0:12:19.062,000 --> 0:12:24,000
(Laughter)

262
0:12:24.434,000 --> 0:12:27,000
You go up to the "File" menu and you choose "New."

263
0:12:27.917,000 --> 0:12:29,000
Now, what happens when you choose "New?"

264
0:12:30.14,000 --> 0:12:32,000
